HEADWORD: Ædile
<hw>⟦AE⟧"dile</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aedilis</ets>, fr. <ets>aedes</ets> temple, public building. Cf.
<er>Edify</er>.]</ety> <def>A magistrate in ancient Rome, who had the
superintendence of public buildings, highways, shows, etc.; hence, a
municipal officer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

